text: Chai Saew Yuen (born 10 June 1969) is a Malaysian taekwondo martial artist. She competed at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the bantamweight event. At the 1988 Asian Taekwondo Championships she won the bronze medal in the -51 kg weight class. == References == Category:1969 births
